XXX. TO VENUS

O Venus, regina Cnidi Paphique

VENUS, of Cnidos and Paphos the queen,

In your well beloved Cyprus no longer be seen 3 But listen, I pray, to my Glycera's call, And breathe the frankincense that burns in her

hall.

Let Cupid come with you, impetuous boy, And the Graces with girdles loosed add to your joy 3 Let the Nymphs corne, and silver-tongued Mercury

too, And Youth —void of beauty or charm without you.
